A non-zero digit is chosen such that the probability of selecting digit $d$ is $\log_{10}(d+2) - \log_{10}(d+1)$. Determine the probability that the digit $3$ is chosen being exactly $1/3$ of the probability that the digit chosen is in the set \{3, 4, 5\}.
A) \{3, 4\}
B) \{4, 5, 6\}
C) \{3, 4, 5\}
D) \{5, 6, 7\}
E) \{6, 7, 8, 9\}
